I took advantage of the New York City Restaurant Week that was offered for set price of $20.21. So I gave Mabel's Smokehouse & Banquet Hall a tryout on take out. Let me say, I was not disappointed in any way.  Let me start by saying, the food was very good in flavor. The meal platters with meat portions and side orders were very generous. Plus they offer you some extra like pickles, coleslaw, pickled jalapenos, slice bread and extra barbecue sauce.  This is a must try and it's highly recommended as well. After this pandemic is over with, I need to come back to give inside dining a try as well.

Rating 3.5  Ribs are small but juicy! Not a ton of meat on them so you can eat all 5 in one sitting. The char I wasnt much of a fan of and skipped around it. The Bbq sauce is not sweet but quite vinegary (not spicy). I wish they also had a sweet & smoky version to choose from. Sides are hefty imo. The collard greens were great! The beans were pretty decent (bacon unnecessary). Wanted cornnbread, but 2 small muffins are $7! Way overpriced when you can buy a whole box of cornbread mix for $0.95.  The outdoor seating was spaced, open for ventilation and had overhead heat lamps! Def a plus. I don't live in the area and wouldn't make a special trip back. The meal was overall decent. More meaty ribs and diff sauce would have made all the difference.
